where xi and yj are the ith input and jth output map, respectively. Kij is a convolutional kernel between the maps i and j, * denotes the convolution operator and bj is the bias parameter of the jth map. The convolutional layer is followed by a max-pooling layer, in which each neuron in the output map yi pools over an SXS non-overlapping region in the input map xi.

